<!--CUT ABOVE-->








Below is a compilation of off-centred crosses (as in many Scandinavian flags), found on flags on this web site.  Note that, although
commonly described as Scandinavian crosses, the flags linked here include many variants from many places in and outside Scandinavia,
and many have little or nothing to do with Scandinavian flag traditions. Fimbriation colours are identified in brackets.  Crosses in
<i>italics</i> are proposals, or flags of uncertain or dubious status.
<ul>
<li><a href="#def">What defines a Scandinavian Cross?</a>
<li><a href="#howmany">How many Scandinavian Cross flags are there?</a>
<li><a href="#related">Related pages</a>
<li><a href="xx-scanm.html">Multicoloured off-centred cross-type flags</a>
</ul>

